# 🔐 How to Reset Root Password (RHEL/CentOS) — GitHub Format

> ⚠️ **Warning:** Physical or console access is required.

## ⭐ Steps

### 1️⃣ Boot into GRUB

1. **Reboot** the system.
2. At the **GRUB menu**, select the kernel you want to boot.
3. Press `e` to **edit** the boot entry.
4. Find the line starting with `linux` or `linux16`.  
   Append `rd.break` to the **end** of this line.
5. Press `Ctrl+x` to boot with these parameters.

---

### 2️⃣ Remount the Filesystem

```bash
mount -o remount,rw /sysroot
chroot /sysroot
```

---

### 3️⃣ Reset the Root Password

```bash
passwd root
```

Enter the new password when prompted.

---

### 4️⃣ Relabel SELinux Contexts

```bash
touch /.autorelabel
```

---

### 5️⃣ Reboot

```bash
exit
exit
reboot
```

> After reboot, the system will relabel files; this may take some time.

---

## 📚 References

- [Red Hat Documentation: Resetting the Root Password](https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_enterprise_linux/8/html-single/security_hardening/index#resetting-the-root-password_security-hardening)


